 1. Get Your Gemini AI Studio API Key
Visit: https://aistudio.google.com

Log in → Click “Get API Key”

Click “Create API Key” or “Use existing project”

Copy and save the API key

🔌 2. Connect to MCP Servers (via Pipedream)
Visit the following MCP server links:

YouTube: YouTube Data MCP Server

Google Drive: Google Drive MCP Server

Notion: Notion MCP Server

Sign in with Google → Authorize → Copy server URL

🛠️ 3. Project Setup Instructions
🧰 Prerequisites
Python 3.10+

Git installed

Cursor IDE or any Python IDE

🧾 Setup Steps with Commands
📁 Step 1: Navigate to Home Directory (Optional)
bash
Copy
Edit
cd ~
🔽 Step 2: Clone or Download the Repo
Option A: Git clone (recommended)

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/learning-path-generator.git
cd learning-path-generator
Option B: ZIP method

Download ZIP from GitHub

Extract it

Open the folder

🧭 Step 3: Open in Cursor IDE
Open Cursor → File → Open Folder → Select the project directory

🧪 Step 4: Create a Virtual Environment
bash
Copy
Edit
python -m venv venv
▶️ Step 5: Activate the Virtual Environment
On Windows (PowerShell):

bash
Copy
Edit
.\venv\Scripts\Activate
On macOS/Linux:

bash
Copy
Edit
source venv/bin/activate
You should now see: (venv) in your terminal

📦 Step 6: Install Required Python Packages
bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
🚀 Step 7: Run the Streamlit App
bash
Copy
Edit
streamlit run app.py
